Options.Doc: Add a field to an event. Default value is {}
Options.Name: AddField

Options.Doc: Extra exchange arguments. Default value is {}
Options.Name: Arguments

Options.Doc: Time in seconds to wait before retrying a connection. Default value is 1
Options.Name: ConnectRetryInterval

Options.Doc: Time in seconds to wait before timing-out. Default value is 0 (no timeout)
Options.Name: ConnectionTimeout

Options.Doc: Is this exchange durable - should it survive a broker restart? Default value is true
Options.Name: Durable

Options.Doc: The name of the exchange to send message to. There is no default value for this setting.
Options.Name: Exchange

Options.Doc: The exchange type (fanout, topic, direct). There is no default value for this setting.
Options.Name: ExchangeType

Options.Doc:
Interval (in second) to send heartbeat to rabbitmq. Default value is 0
If value if lower than 1, server's interval setting will be used.
Options.Name: Heartbeat

Options.Doc: RabbitMQ server address. There is no default value for this setting.
Options.Name: Host

Options.Doc:
The routing key to use when binding a queue to the exchange. Default value is ""
This is only relevant for direct or topic exchanges (Routing keys are ignored on fanout exchanges).
This setting can be dynamic using the %{foo} syntax.
Options.Name: Key

Options.Doc:
Use queue passively declared, meaning it must already exist on the server. Default value is false
To have BitFan to create the queue if necessary leave this option as false.
If actively declaring a queue that already exists, the queue options for this plugin (durable, etc) must match those of the existing queue.
Options.Name: Passive

Options.Doc: Should RabbitMQ persist messages to disk? Default value is true
Options.Name: Persistent

Options.Doc: RabbitMQ port to connect on. Default value is 5672
Options.Name: Port

Options.Doc: Enable or disable SSL. Default value is false
Options.Name: SSL

Options.Doc:
Add any number of arbitrary tags to your event. There is no default value for this setting.
This can help with processing later. Tags can be dynamic and include parts of the event using the %{field} syntax.
Options.Name: Tags

Options.Doc: Validate SSL certificate. Default value is false
Options.Name: VerifySSL

Options.Doc: The vhost to use. Default value is "/"
Options.Name: Vhost
